parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbags to Deploy in Crash Situations
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in crash situations can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality to occupants, as well as increased damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in crash situations
despite the severity of the impact
resulting in injuries or fatalities to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Engine Control Unit (ECU) can cause the Vehicle Stability Control (VSC) and Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) lights to come on, leading to a loss of traction and stability, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: and brake lights are illuminated on the dashboard
and the vehicle may experience a loss of traction and stability.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Undersized Brake Caliper and Rotor Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The undersized brake caliper and rotor issues can cause the vehicle to vibrate violently when applying the brakes, leading to overheating, warping, and excessive wear on the rotors, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes violently when applying the brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, and in some cases, may not deploy airbags, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience brake failure
leading to a loss of control

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden standard transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the gear shift bracket and lever break
the vehicle creeps while in forward or reverse gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission bearing failure can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the bearings inside the transmission go bad

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: SMT creeping can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The SMT creeps while in forward or reverse gear

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission thumping or jerking can cause the vehicle to lose power or control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: A "thump" or jerking sensation is felt when taking foot off the brake pedal to start moving forward

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission safety lock failure can cause the vehicle to shift into the wrong gear, leading to accidents or engine damage.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into the wrong gear
there is no safety lock preventing the vehicle from shifting into the wrong gear.
